{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fb4ce938-9e00-4937-8763-81e6cf293517","content":"Here's what to update:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**4. Install the SDK** — Download .NET 11 SDK from https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/11.0 (or update your package manager).\n\n**5. Restore & build** to catch any breaking changes:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nAlso review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) for any breaking API or behavioral changes that may affect your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ff725f39-e9fd-4959-bb29-4b451360b4c9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no codebase to explore.","outputTokens":326,"requestId":"4010:20FADF:167EF23:195090B:69F94AD9"},"id":"5bfaf97c-f746-401e-ac21-2d389cda2fd3","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:41:52.369Z","parentId":"288009df-c5ca-4ca4-a0bc-02d2d087ac0a"}
